WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:04.386 --> 00:00:05.307
(fire alarm beeping)

2
00:00:05.308 --> 00:00:08.360
What the hell is going on?

3
00:00:08.428 --> 00:00:10.095
Come on. what'd you do?

4
00:00:10.163 --> 00:00:11.930
I was trying to
make pancakes.

5
00:00:11.999 --> 00:00:13.565
What. barbecued pancakes?

6
00:00:13.634 --> 00:00:15.400
Jack always made
it look so easy;

7
00:00:15.469 --> 00:00:17.035
I thought it might be
a nice surprise.

8
00:00:17.104 --> 00:00:19.137
Well. it was a nice attempt
at a surprise.

9
00:00:19.206 --> 00:00:21.339
Jack and I had
our own traditions.

10
00:00:21.408 --> 00:00:22.774
You and I will make
our own. too.

11
00:00:22.843 --> 00:00:24.523
- If you say so.
- Come on. you're gonna be

12
00:00:24.578 --> 00:00:26.578
late for school; let's go. hurry up.
(sighs)

13
00:00:26.647 --> 00:00:27.991
Did you speak
to your brother today?

14
00:00:28.015 --> 00:00:30.135
It's 8:00 a.m.. do you think
I've spoken with him yet?

15
00:00:30.183 --> 00:00:31.663
Well. I tried to reach him
last night.

16
00:00:31.718 --> 00:00:32.984
and he never got back to me.

17
00:00:33.053 --> 00:00:36.154
Yeah. he posted some picture
from a party last night.

18
00:00:36.223 --> 00:00:37.656
Party?

19
00:00:37.724 --> 00:00:38.945
Who the hell has a party
on a Sunday night?

20
00:00:38.969 --> 00:00:40.700
Beats me; ask him.

21
00:00:42.663 --> 00:00:43.959
You came over with the
new sergeant. right?

22
00:00:43.983 --> 00:00:44.931
Yeah.

23
00:00:44.932 --> 00:00:46.865
He was my partner
in the 12th.

24
00:00:46.934 --> 00:00:49.834
He was your partner?

25
00:00:49.903 --> 00:00:51.503
That must've been tough.

26
00:00:51.572 --> 00:00:53.171
What do you mean?

27
00:00:53.240 --> 00:00:56.107
He's so tightly wound.
and. I mean. come on.

28
00:00:56.176 --> 00:00:57.442
he clearly thinks
he's the man

29
00:00:57.511 --> 00:00:59.210
on the account of
he's the PC's son.

30
00:00:59.279 --> 00:01:00.612
- No.
- Yeah.

31
00:01:00.681 --> 00:01:02.814
Well. he has to
be that way

32
00:01:02.883 --> 00:01:06.418
because he
inherited a mess.

33
00:01:06.486 --> 00:01:07.752
What "mess"?

34
00:01:07.821 --> 00:01:10.188
I've been with the 2-9
three years. I'm no mess.

35
00:01:10.257 --> 00:01:13.825
Oh. hey. that's not
what I meant. I just...

36
00:01:13.894 --> 00:01:16.428
Listen. is this the only
precinct you've ever been in?

37
00:01:16.496 --> 00:01:18.997
- Yeah. why?
- Well. then it's what you know.

38
00:01:19.066 --> 00:01:20.443
But there are different
ways to do things.

39
00:01:20.467 --> 00:01:23.001
To do what?
To get more collars?

40
00:01:23.070 --> 00:01:25.370
No. it's not just
about making collars.

41
00:01:25.439 --> 00:01:26.482
It's about doing
what's best

42
00:01:26.506 --> 00:01:27.684
for the people in
your neighborhood.

43
00:01:27.708 --> 00:01:29.040
That's what I
always try to do.

44
00:01:29.109 --> 00:01:31.054
Well. good. then we're
gonna get along great. - Okay.

45
00:01:31.078 --> 00:01:32.010
(pounding on door)

46
00:01:32.079 --> 00:01:33.912
Hey. Hey!
(man shouting in Spanish)

47
00:01:33.981 --> 00:01:36.815
(both shouting in Spanish)

48
00:01:36.883 --> 00:01:38.583
(grunts)

49
00:01:38.652 --> 00:01:39.862
MAYA: Whoa. whoa.
step away from the door!

50
00:01:39.886 --> 00:01:42.053
(speaking Spanish)

51
00:01:43.724 --> 00:01:45.368
Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa.
(Janko speaking Spanish)

52
00:01:45.392 --> 00:01:46.458
What are you doing?

53
00:01:46.526 --> 00:01:49.561
I'm sorry. it's...
(inhales sharply)

54
00:01:49.630 --> 00:01:51.240
I'm just upset about the
lottery. it's nothing.

55
00:01:51.264 --> 00:01:52.864
It's nothing?
We've got you on dis con

56
00:01:52.933 --> 00:01:54.133
and criminal mischief already.

57
00:01:54.167 --> 00:01:56.112
And you were about to throw
that through the glass.

58
00:01:56.136 --> 00:01:58.081
No. he just lost his temper;
it's a little misunderstanding.

59
00:01:58.105 --> 00:01:59.571
- We're good. <i>Estamos bien.</i>
- Yeah?

60
00:01:59.640 --> 00:02:01.117
He doesn't look so good;
so what's this beef about?

61
00:02:01.141 --> 00:02:03.775
No beef.
just a neighborhood thing.

62
00:02:03.844 --> 00:02:05.510
Yeah. well. this is
our neighborhood. too.

63
00:02:05.579 --> 00:02:07.946
so what's the thing?

64
00:02:08.015 --> 00:02:09.614
It's the lotto.

65
00:02:10.951 --> 00:02:14.519
Look. are gonna walk away
and leave this man alone?

66
00:02:14.588 --> 00:02:15.620
I promise.

67
00:02:15.689 --> 00:02:17.088
That good by you?

68
00:02:17.157 --> 00:02:18.490
Yeah. Yeah. yeah.
it's good.

69
00:02:18.558 --> 00:02:19.836
- <i>Estamos bien.</i>
-All right. then.

70
00:02:19.860 --> 00:02:20.992
Get lost.

71
00:02:23.497 --> 00:02:24.896
- "Get lost"?
- What?

72
00:02:24.965 --> 00:02:26.831
He calmed down;
he didn't look like

73
00:02:26.900 --> 00:02:28.233
a danger to himself
or others.

74
00:02:28.301 --> 00:02:30.146
You want to put him in the system over
a lotto ticket thing?

75
00:02:30.170 --> 00:02:32.382
- No. I don't to put him in the system...
- Take a look around.

76
00:02:32.406 --> 00:02:35.540
What do you see?

77
00:02:35.609 --> 00:02:38.276
- Rubberneckers.
- Documentary filmmakers.

78
00:02:38.345 --> 00:02:39.944
You want to star
in a movie called

79
00:02:40.013 --> 00:02:43.415
<i>Cops Overreacting?</i>
- No. you do not.

80
00:02:49.556 --> 00:02:51.623
Oh. good morning.
Inspector.

81
00:02:51.692 --> 00:02:54.826
Inspector Kimura is here. sir.

82
00:02:56.163 --> 00:02:57.929
- He will be right with you.
- Thank you.

83
00:02:57.998 --> 00:02:59.798
Congratulations
on your promotion.

84
00:02:59.866 --> 00:03:01.700
- I appreciate that.
- Of course.

85
00:03:01.768 --> 00:03:04.736
Morning. Please.

86
00:03:04.805 --> 00:03:06.638
Good morning. Commissioner.

87
00:03:15.015 --> 00:03:16.881
Couple more days.

88
00:03:16.950 --> 00:03:19.190
You want me to call you Deputy
Chief. try it on for size?

89
00:03:19.252 --> 00:03:20.885
(chuckles)
Wouldn't want to jinx it. sir.

90
00:03:20.954 --> 00:03:23.388
Huh. Good thinking.

91
00:03:23.457 --> 00:03:24.689
Coffee?

92
00:03:24.758 --> 00:03:27.792
No. thanks.

93
00:03:27.861 --> 00:03:29.694
Okay. What's up?

94
00:03:29.763 --> 00:03:31.463
Static I'm hearing.

95
00:03:31.531 --> 00:03:32.897
About?

96
00:03:32.966 --> 00:03:34.833
Specifically. my promotion.

97
00:03:34.901 --> 00:03:36.568
Well. let me
stop you right there.

98
00:03:36.636 --> 00:03:38.136
There's always gonna be somebody

99
00:03:38.205 --> 00:03:40.305
who thinks they were
passed over unfairly.

100
00:03:40.373 --> 00:03:42.540
I'm afraid that goes
with the territory. Jane.

101
00:03:42.609 --> 00:03:45.176
This someone is planning
to put in his papers

102
00:03:45.245 --> 00:03:46.344
and file a lawsuit.

103
00:03:46.413 --> 00:03:47.979
(sighs) And you know this how?

104
00:03:48.048 --> 00:03:49.214
Sources in the department

105
00:03:49.282 --> 00:03:51.182
and in the Captain's
Benevolent Association.

106
00:03:51.251 --> 00:03:54.185
About a candidate
on your short list.

107
00:03:54.254 --> 00:03:55.520
Named?

108
00:03:55.589 --> 00:03:59.124
I'd rather not say. sir.

109
00:03:59.192 --> 00:04:01.426
I assume the short list
was indeed short

110
00:04:01.495 --> 00:04:03.828
and that your sources
are even better than mine.

111
00:04:03.897 --> 00:04:06.531
Good thinking.

112
00:04:06.600 --> 00:04:10.502
As an Asian female. I don't have
much of a tribe in the NYPD.

113
00:04:10.570 --> 00:04:13.705
but the friends I do have
are very protective

114
00:04:13.774 --> 00:04:15.974
and very proactive on my behalf.

115
00:04:16.042 --> 00:04:18.343
I know. I'm one of them.

116
00:04:18.411 --> 00:04:20.645
I know.

117
00:04:20.714 --> 00:04:24.182
Is this. in any way.

118
00:04:24.251 --> 00:04:26.718
putting you off
accepting your promotion?

119
00:04:26.787 --> 00:04:29.687
Not in any way. sir.

120
00:04:29.756 --> 00:04:34.259
Good. Good.

121
00:04:34.327 --> 00:04:36.194
I'll look into it.

122
00:04:36.263 --> 00:04:38.530
Thank you. Commissioner.

123
00:04:42.135 --> 00:04:44.602
(door opens. closes)

124
00:04:48.809 --> 00:04:51.209
- What do we got?
- One student DOA.

125
00:04:51.278 --> 00:04:52.610
18 years old. freshman.

126
00:04:52.679 --> 00:04:53.711
Kid got a name?

127
00:04:53.780 --> 00:04:55.013
Peter Jones.

128
00:04:55.081 --> 00:04:57.682
What the hell is with
these kids partying on a Sunday?

129
00:04:57.751 --> 00:05:00.118
They say it started as a darty.
lasted into the night.

130
00:05:00.187 --> 00:05:01.419
- A what?
- A darty.

131
00:05:01.488 --> 00:05:03.021
Short for "day party."

132
00:05:03.089 --> 00:05:04.189
Oh. my God.

133
00:05:08.461 --> 00:05:11.396
BAEZ: This place is disgusting;
guys actually live here?

134
00:05:11.464 --> 00:05:14.933
Guys actually compete to live
here. believe it or not.

135
00:05:15.001 --> 00:05:18.570
I had no idea there was Greek
life at Hudson University.

136
00:05:19.840 --> 00:05:21.506
There won't be anymore.

137
00:05:21.575 --> 00:05:23.308
Not after this.

138
00:05:30.083 --> 00:05:34.083
